[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcampaign. AddressSanitizer reported an out-of-bounds write in the function [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`htmlSecureComment` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min HTMLparser.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when processing a specially crafted input [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munder the HTML fuzz harness. The overflow occurs while copying data into a heap [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation that is too small for the amount of data being written.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Issue Type**  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The issue is a heap-buffer-overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmulti-byte write[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m detected by [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer in libxml2’s HTML parsing code.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Failure Manifestation**  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  During a fuzzing run [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`run_fuzzer html -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the following error[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas emitted:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow at `__asan_memcpy`  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • Faulting write size: [0m[1;36m105[0m[39m bytes  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • Faulty destination: a heap buffer of [0m[1;36m501[0m[39m bytes, with the overflow starting [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexactly at the end of the allocated region.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Relevant Stack Trace**  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `__asan_memcpy` interceptor  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `htmlSecureComment` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mHTMLparser.[0m[1;92mc:3591[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Observations and Findings**  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The overflow is triggered by `memcpy` in `htmlSecureComment`, suggesting a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmismatch between the buffer allocation size [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m501[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the amount of data [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbeing copied [0m[1;39m([0m[39mat least [0m[1;36m105[0m[39m bytes beyond the end[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The allocation is performed via `xmlFuzzMalloc`, which ultimately calls [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`malloc`, and the same function [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`htmlSecureComment`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m both allocates and writes to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe buffer.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The error consistently reproduces under the libFuzzer harness, indicating a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeterministic parsing path in the HTML comment handling code.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Code Areas for Investigation**  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. **htmlSecureComment [0m[1;39m([0m[39mHTMLparser.c around line [0m[1;36m3591[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**  [0m                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhtml -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA fuzzing harness against libxml2’s HTML parser [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`HTMLparser.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m triggered an [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow inside the function `htmlSecureComment`. The [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow occurs during a multi‐byte `memcpy` when combining input chunks and [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreplacement data into a buffer without adequate bounds checks or reallocation. [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn attempted patch modified two code regions in `HTMLparser.c` to tighten the size [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks and adjust reallocation logic:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In one region [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m2827[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the check was changed from `extraSize > [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaxLength - used` to `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mused + extraSize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > maxLength` and similarly for [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`buffer_size`.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In a second region [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m3572[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the patch reorganized the computation of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`extraSize` and its bounds checks in relation to `buffer_size`.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the build fails with numerous “undeclared identifier” [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `skip`, `replSize`, `repl`, `input`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, misplaced labels and `break` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstatements, and missing context for `goto error`. This indicates the diff did not [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malign correctly with the surrounding code, introducing references to variables and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlabels out of scope.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Initial Issue**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzer output shows an AddressSanitizer error in `htmlSecureComment` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`HTMLparser.[0m[1;92mc:3591[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The error is a heap-buffer-overflow during a `memcpy` of size [0m[1;36m105[0m[39m bytes just [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpast the end of a [0m[1;36m501[0m[39m-byte allocation.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack trace highlights calls:  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     htmlSecureComment → htmlTopParseComment → htmlParseDocument → [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhtmlCtxtParseDocument → LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The allocated buffer resides at `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x[0m[33m...[0m[1;36m580[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0x[0m[33m...[0m[1;36m775[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`; the write target [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;36m0x[0m[33m...[0m[1;36m775[0m[39m` is immediately out of that range.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Key Observations from the Fuzz Log**  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer runs with `libFuzzer` and `AddressSanitizer`.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only one input module is loaded; the overflow occurs the first time the input [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis processed.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The faulty `memcpy` is invoked without sufficient reallocation or bounds [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecking against `buffer_size` or `maxLength`.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Patch Attempt**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The submitted patch provides two hunks:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Hunk A** [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround original line [0m[1;36m2827[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ‑ Changed  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mextraSize > maxLength - used[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mextraSize > buffer_size - used[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     to  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mused + extraSize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > maxLength[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mused + extraSize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > buffer_size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     and doubled the new size during reallocation.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Hunk B** [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround original line [0m[1;36m3572[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ‑ Introduced recomputation of `extraSize = chunkSize + replSize`  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ‑ Wrapped the growth check in `if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mused + extraSize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > buffer_size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ‑ Attempted to preserve the old logic for copying `chunk` into `buffer`.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Result of Applying the Patch**  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The build fails with errors indicating the patch’s context is misaligned.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Error examples:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • “use of undeclared identifier ‘skip’”  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • “use of undeclared identifier ‘replSize’ [0m[35m/[0m[39m ‘repl’”  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • “‘break’ statement not in loop or switch”  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Missing `error:` label for `goto error`  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Unknown type name `input`  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Warnings for unused parameters [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`maxLength`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m suggest this function signature [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmay differ from what the patch assumed.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The number and nature of errors show that variable names and control-flow [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlabels in the patch do not correspond to those in the actual source at that [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocation.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Areas for Further Investigation**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The implementation of `htmlSecureComment` and its local variables: confirm the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnames and scopes of `chunk`, `skip`, `repl`, `replSize`, `buffer`, `used`, and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`buffer_size`.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The definition and intended semantics of `maxLength` and how it should guard [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magainst unbounded growth.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Surrounding control flow: locate the correct `error:` label and the loop or [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mswitch that governs `break` statements.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Compare with similar resizing logic elsewhere in `HTMLparser.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., in [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mother parsing functions[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify that the patch hunks target the correct file offsets and function [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msignatures.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis report outlines the original memory-safety failure, the structure of the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempted fix, and the compilation breakdown following the patch. A careful review [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof the function’s actual layout and variable definitions in `HTMLparser.c` is [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrequired before reapplying any size-check or reallocation changes.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`memcpy`.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The write of [0m[1;36m105[0m[39m bytes occurs at the exact end of a [0m[1;36m501[0m[39m-byte region, indicating[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man off-by-bounds condition.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Stack trace leads from `htmlSecureComment` → `htmlTopParseComment` → [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`htmlParseDocument` → `htmlCtxtParseDocument` → `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The buffer in question was allocated by `xmlFuzzMalloc` for comment handling [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand is too small for the combination of `chunkSize` plus replacement size.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant observations in the initial log  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The “[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes after [0m[1;36m501[0m[39m-byte region” message shows the overwrite starts [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately past the allocated area.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The sanitizer shadow-byte legend confirms a heap left redzone violation.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Both `chunkSize` and a replacement size [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`replSize`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m factor into the overflow.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The error occurs consistently in the comment-parsing routines of HTMLparser.c.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Two hunk locations were targeted: one at line ~[0m[1;36m2827[0m[39m and another at ~[0m[1;36m3572[0m[39m.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In each hunk the condition `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mextraSize > buffer_size – used[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` was rewritten as[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mused + extraSize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > buffer_size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, and an analogous change was made for [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`maxLength`.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch attempted to recompute `extraSize` and to call `xmlRealloc` on `buffer`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mused + extraSize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > buffer_size`, updating `buffer` and `buffer_size`.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Surrounding code for copying `chunk` to `buffer` and advancing `input->cur` was [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleft in place or slightly reorganized.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCompilation result after patch  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The compiler reported dozens of errors in HTMLparser.c:  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Identifiers `skip`, `replSize`, `repl`, `used`, `input`, `ctxt`, `ret` are [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mundeclared in the patched sections.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - A `break` was placed outside any loop or `switch`.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The `error` label [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtarget of `goto error`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is not in scope.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The patch introduced code at positions that no longer match existing variable [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclarations or control-flow blocks.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Several function parameters [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `maxLength`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m became unused or mismatched.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a heap-buffer-overflow detected by AddressSanitizer in [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibxml2’s HTML parser, specifically in the function `htmlSecureComment` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcalled by [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`htmlTopParseComment`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The fuzzer log shows a write past the end of a [0m[1;36m501[0m[39m-byte [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap allocation when copying [0m[1;36m105[0m[39m bytes.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn attempted patch introduced additional bounds checks against `maxLength` and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madjusted the logic for resizing the `buffer` when `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mused + extraSize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer_size`.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the code fails to compile with about [0m[1;36m20[0m[39m errors—undeclared[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentifiers [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`skip`, `replSize`, `repl`, `input`, `termSkip`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, missing the `error` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlabel, and misuse of variables [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`used`, `ctxt`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, indicating that the patch’s hunks [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwere mis-scoped or misaligned with the existing code.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A fuzzing session of the `html` binary [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuilt from libxml2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m triggered an ASAN [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merror at `__asan_memcpy` inside `htmlSecureComment` in `HTMLparser.[0m[1;92mc:3591[0m[39m`.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The log reports a multi-byte write out of bounds: the code attempts to write [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m105[0m[39m bytes at offset [0m[1;36m501[0m[39m of an allocation that spans bytes [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…[0m[1;36m580[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…[0m[1;36m775[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow is traced back to a combination of `chunkSize` and `replSize` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexceeding the remaining space in the buffer.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack shows the failure propagates up through `htmlTopParseComment`, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`htmlParseDocument`, and the fuzz harness entry point `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Two hunks were added to `HTMLparser.c`:  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Around line [0m[1;36m2827[0m[39m: replace  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        “if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mextraSize > maxLength - used[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m”  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        with  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        “if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mused + extraSize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > maxLength[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m”,  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        and similarly adjust the `buffer_size` check to use `used + extraSize > [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer_size`.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Around line [0m[1;36m3572[0m[39m: re-compute `extraSize` after parsing `chunkSize`, insert [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma `maxLength` check that calls `htmlParseErr` and `goto error` if exceeded, then [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguard the resize logic with `if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mused + extraSize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > buffer_size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The intent was to prevent unbounded growth and enforce resource limits before [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcopying data into the buffer.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Result and Compilation Errors  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After applying the diff, compilation errors occur in `HTMLparser.c` at and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maround the newly patched region:  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Use of undeclared identifiers: `skip`, `replSize`, `repl`, `input`, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`termSkip`, `used`, `ctxt`.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Implicit-int declarations and mismatched types.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The errors indicate that the diff did not align with the actual variable [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclarations or control-flow structure in that function, removing or relocating [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcritical context needed to refer to those names.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
